Here are the MSTest 3.x+ patterns for each scenario:

**1. Windows-only (registry)** — `[OSCondition]` (MSTest 3.10+):
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
public void Registry_ReadsExpectedValue()
{
    var value = Registry.GetValue(@"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\MyApp", "Version", null);
    Assert.IsNotNull(value);
}
```

**2. Skip in CI (local GPU required)** — `[CICondition]` (MSTest 3.10+):
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]
public void RenderFrame_UsesGpuAcceleration()
{
    var renderer = new GpuRenderer();
    var frame = renderer.Render();
    Assert.IsNotNull(frame);
}
```

**3. Flaky external API** — `[Retry]` (MSTest 3.9+):
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)]
[Timeout(10000)]
public async Task WeatherApi_ReturnsForecast()
{
    var forecast = await _weatherClient.GetForecastAsync(_testContext.CancellationToken);
    Assert.IsNotNull(forecast);
}
```
Use `[Retry]` only for genuinely flaky external dependencies — not to mask race conditions or shared-state bugs.

**4. Cleanup temp files even on failure** — `[TestCleanup]` + `IDisposable`:
```csharp
[TestClass]
public sealed class FileProcessorTests : IDisposable
{
    private readonly string _tempFile;

    public FileProcessorTests()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void ProcessFile_WritesExpectedOutput()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "test data");
        var result = FileProcessor.Process(_tempFile);
        Assert.AreEqual("processed", result);
    }

    [TestCleanup]
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
        {
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
        }
    }

    public void Dispose() => Cleanup();
}
```

`[TestCleanup]` runs after every test regardless of pass/fail. Implementing `IDisposable` adds a safety net.

**Key takeaways:**
- `[OSCondition]` and `[CICondition]` **skip** tests (not fail) when conditions aren't met
- `[Retry(n)]` re-runs up to `n` times on failure — pair with `[Timeout]` and `CancellationToken`
- `[TestCleanup]` is guaranteed to run even when a test throws
